Add a function that probes Ollama by attempting a TCP connection to `127.0.0.1:11434` with a 1-second timeout, per `specs/packaging.md`:

```rust
fn ollama_available() -> bool {
    use std::net::TcpStream;
    use std::time::Duration;
    TcpStream::connect_timeout(
        &"127.0.0.1:11434".parse().unwrap(),
        Duration::from_secs(1),
    ).is_ok()
}
```

Connection-only: no data is sent. Returns `true` if the connection succeeds (Ollama is running), `false` on any error.

In `run_pipeline_inner()` in `src/app.rs`, inside the `if !config.selected_prompt.is_empty()` branch, immediately before the `run_llm_collect()` call, add:

```rust
if !ollama_available() {
    anyhow::bail!(
        "Ollama not running. Start Ollama and try again.\n\
         Run `ollama serve` in a terminal, or open the Ollama app."
    );
}
```

The error propagates as `AppEvent::PipelineDone(Err(...))`, which the existing handler displays as an NSAlert and transitions back to Idle. The probe is skipped entirely when `selected_prompt` is empty ('No Prompt' mode), per the spec.
